        <p class="mb-4">
          Our <strong>Die with Zero calculator</strong> is the most comprehensive free tool available for optimizing your retirement decumulation strategy. Whether you are a newly retired early retiree wondering how much you can safely spend, or a seasoned FIRE enthusiast looking to transition from accumulation to decumulation, this calculator provides accurate, instant projections tailored to your financial situation and life expectancy.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Why Choose Die with Zero?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4">
          The traditional retirement planning paradigm — save as much as possible, then spend conservatively using the 4% rule — leaves enormous amounts of money unspent. Research from the Employee Benefit Research Institute shows that <strong>retirees with $1M+ portfolios typically die with 80% of their pre-retirement wealth intact</strong>. The 4% rule was designed to survive the worst historical market periods, which means in average or good markets, you die with significantly more than you started with.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          The Die with Zero philosophy asks a simple question: <strong>What if you could spend all of it?</strong> By using the Time Value of Money to calculate your optimal annual withdrawal, you can enjoy 40-60% more spending during the years when you are healthy, active, and can actually enjoy the experiences money buys. An extra $20,000 per year in your 60s and 70s funds trips with grandchildren, hobbies you have always wanted to pursue, or relocating to your dream location.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          This approach is particularly powerful for <strong>FIRE retirees</strong> who optimized their savings rate for years but now find themselves unsure how to transition to spending mode. The psychological shift from aggressive saver to intentional spender is one of the hardest parts of early retirement. Die with Zero provides the mathematical framework — and permission — to enjoy your hard-earned portfolio.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Key Features of This Die with Zero Calculator</h3>

        <p class="mb-4">
          See your <strong>optimal annual spend</strong> instantly as you adjust inputs — the single most important number that tells you how much you can withdraw each year. The calculator supports both <strong>linear (even)</strong> and <strong>front-loaded</strong> spending curves, so you can model the reality that you will likely spend more in your active early retirement years and less later. The <strong>4% rule comparison</strong> feature shows exactly how much money the traditional approach leaves on the table — often a shocking six-figure difference.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          The interactive <strong>portfolio projection chart</strong> visualizes your portfolio balance declining over time, reaching your target buffer at your chosen death age. Adjust your <strong>end-of-life buffer</strong> to see how even a modest reserve of $25K–$50K affects your annual spending (spoiler: very little, because it is deeply discounted by compounding). Whether you want to leave nothing behind, a small buffer, or a meaningful inheritance, the calculator gives you the exact numbers you need to plan with confidence — completely free, no signup required.
        </p>
